label a4_s18_noelle_route_choose:

    a "You want to and you want to not think."

    n "Yes."

    a "And you want me to choose."

    n "Yes. I know what I am asking. I am asking you to do the decision-making for the first ten seconds of a scene in which I have just said that decision-making is the compromised skill. I know."

    n "I am asking anyway. Because the decision I am trying to not make is a decision about which version of my own want is admissible, and the only way to not make that decision is to have someone else make it. If you choose, the decision is out of my framework, because the framework does not include 'Aeron chose' as a variable I can manipulate."

    n "I am asking you to be the non-framework."

    "A long beat. He is reading her face. The blue is on her right cheek. The strip-light is on her left."

    athought "She is asking me to choose for her in a scene in which I am not supposed to be performing usefulness. That is a paradox. The paradox is the scene."

    athought "I am going to choose the option that is kindest to the paradox."

    athought "The option that is kindest to the paradox is not 'here' — here is the corridor option and the corridor is a statement of want-without-infrastructure and she is not asking for a statement of want-without-infrastructure, she is asking for the infrastructure to stop being the thing she is doing the wanting with."

    athought "The option that is kindest is the room she came from. Her room. Her bed. The datapad on the desk."

    athought "Because the infrastructure she needs tonight is not the infrastructure of a bed — it is the infrastructure of a room that is hers, where she has been alone a thousand times, and tonight I am in it, and the 'I am in it' is the new variable."

    a "Somewhere we can stay."

    a "Your quarters. Your bed. Your datapad on the desk. We are going to walk there. You are not going to pick the datapad up when we pass it. And we are going to be in your room with the door closed."

    "A beat."

    n "Why that one."

    a "Because the version of not-thinking you are asking for is not the version where we stand against a corridor wall and fall through our own hunger. That version would be a different kind of not-thinking. The version you are asking for is the version where you are in the room where you do your classifying, and you are not classifying, and my body is the thing in the room that is making the not-classifying possible."

    a "I want to be that thing. I am not useful in that version. I am furniture. Furniture in the room where the framework lives, furniture that is taking up the space the framework used to take up."

    a "That is what I choose."

    n "That is a very strange sentence."

    a "I know."

    n "It is also the right one."

    a "I know."

    "She takes his hand. Her fingers are cold."

    "They walk the long way back. She does not look at the walls. He does not try to speak."

    "They arrive at her door. She opens it. The datapad is on the desk. She walks past it."

    "She closes the door behind him."

    # [INTIMATE CONTENT HERE]
    # (User writes this beat. Noelle erotic deepening — her room,
    # her bed, with the added weight of having explicitly delegated
    # the choice to him. The grammar is that he chose the room
    # where her framework lives and then refused to be useful
    # inside it — he is furniture. The not-thinking is the
    # substance of the scene. His presence is the weight of a man
    # who is refusing to classify her back. Do not cut to aftercare
    # until the body of the scene is complete on its own terms.)

    jump a4_s18_noelle_aftercare_intimate

label a4_s18_noelle_aftercare_intimate:

    # ========== PHASE 7 — AFTERCARE ==========

    # CAMERA: 50mm. Her face. The datapad is in frame somewhere —
    # on the desk, or on the floor if the corridor-route, or absent
    # from the corridor scene entirely — depending on route. She is
    # not looking at it. The camera is on her face and on the small
    # distance between their mouths.
    # LIGHTING: Whichever room the route arrived in. Low.
    # SFX: Her breath. His breath. No music. At the very end: the
    # single held low string from s13a, the one that did not
    # resolve, resolving on a new note. Not the old note. A new one.

    "A long quiet."

    "Her hand is on his chest again — one hand this time, flat, at the place above his heart. Her other hand is against her own mouth, fingers curled loosely, the way a person holds a thing they have just said and want to keep for a moment."

    "He is on his side, facing her."

    "She is not looking at him. She is looking at the ceiling — or the wall, or the corridor's far end, depending on which route got them here — and her face is doing something he has not seen on her face before, which is the face of a woman who has just spent forty minutes inside an experience that did not have a rubric and is discovering that the experience did not collapse."

    "She did not collapse."

    "The absence of the framework did not destroy her. The framework was a scaffolding, and the scaffolding has been gone for forty minutes, and she is still here, and there is a man beside her whose hand is on her stomach, and the hand is not classifying her."

    nthought "I am going to say it."

    nthought "I said it two weeks ago. I said it as a variable. I said it in the register of a framework that was still intact, and I said it in the part of the framework labeled 'data I am delivering to Aeron as an input to his decision about us.'"

    nthought "I am going to say it again."

    nthought "I am going to say it as a sentence this time."

    nthought "I do not know what the difference is between a variable and a sentence. I have not been trained in that distinction. I am going to try the distinction by speaking."

    "She lowers the hand from her mouth."

    "She speaks."

    n "I love you."

    "A beat."

    n "I said that two weeks ago."

    n "I said it as a variable. I flagged it. I told you what it was. I put it in quotes. I said 'I am telling you this as data' and then I gave you the data and then I waited to see what the classification system would do with the return value."

    n "I am saying it now as a sentence."

    n "I am not flagging it. I am not putting it in quotes. I am not telling you that I am saying it as a sentence so that you know the register — I am telling you that I am saying it as a sentence so that you know that I know there is a difference, and I have decided to cross the difference, and I am crossing it in this room in front of you while your hand is on my stomach and the framework that would have classified this sentence is on the other side of the room or back in my workspace or nowhere, depending on which room we are in."

    n "It is a sentence."

    n "The sentence does not have a variable. The sentence has a subject and a verb and an object. The subject is me. The verb is love. The object is you. The sentence is complete in itself without a rubric attached to it."

    "A beat."

    n "I did not know I could say that sentence."

    n "I said it."

    n "It is still in the room."

    n "It did not explode. I did not need to classify it afterwards. The world did not require me to put a register on it within thirty seconds of saying it or else I would have felt like the sentence was uncontained. I am watching the sentence be in the room and the sentence is — staying."

    n "The sentence is staying in the room with me and with you and I am not having to do anything with it."

    n "I am going to have to learn how to live in a world where sentences stay in a room without me containing them."

    n "I am going to have to unlearn thirty-one years of containing sentences."

    n "I am going to do it with you in the room."

    n "Not because I need you in the room. I do not know whether I need you in the room. I am not going to know that for a while. I want you in the room. The want is the sentence. The want is the thing I am taking out of this scene."

    "A long beat."

    "He does not classify it back. He does not respond with a taxonomy of his own. He does the thing she has been asking him to do by asking him to be furniture — he is the weight of a man who is present and is not arranging her sentences into categories."

    "He moves his hand from her stomach to her face."

    "He turns her face toward him with his palm — not forcing, inviting — and when her eyes meet his he says the only sentence he is going to say in the aftercare."

    a "I heard you."

    a "I am not going to classify it back. I am going to let it be in the room. And I am going to be in the room with it and with you."

    "A beat."

    a "I love you too."

    a "As a sentence. Not as data. I am saying it the way you just said it. The subject is me. The verb is love. The object is you. I did not have the register for that sentence two weeks ago. I have it tonight because you showed me the shape of it just now, and I am going to say it back to you in the shape you gave me."

    "She closes her eyes."

    "She does not cry. Noelle does not cry — the crying-register is not one she has an operational file for yet and she is not going to start tonight. But her breath changes. The breath becomes the breath of a woman who has been holding a thirty-one-year-old scaffolding together and has been told, by another person in the same room, that she does not have to hold it together alone."

    "She puts her face into the side of his neck."

    "She stays there."

    "The room holds the sentence."

    "The sentence does not move."

    "Fade."

    jump a4_s18_noelle_scene_close

label a4_s18_noelle_scene_close:

    # stop ambient fadeout 4.0
    # scene black with fade

    # ========= STATE UPDATES =========
    $ rel_bump("Noelle", trust=2, attraction=2)
    $ canon_set("noelle.framework_broken", True)
    $ canon_set("noelle.said_love_as_sentence", True)
    $ canon_set("noelle.acquired_want_as_framework", True)
    $ flag("noelle_left_her_quarters_without_datapad", True)
    $ flag("noelle_erotic_deepening_emp", True)
    $ npc_remember("Noelle", "found_in_corridor_without_datapad", tone="unscaffolded")
    $ npc_remember("Noelle", "asked_what_if_not_useful", tone="paradox_of_request")
    $ npc_remember("Noelle", "said_it_as_a_sentence", tone="crossed_the_difference")
    $ npc_remember("Aeron", "answered_i_dont_know", tone="true_not_knowing")
    $ tp_seed("a4.noelle.said_it_as_sentence")
    $ tp_seed("a4.noelle.corridor_without_framework")
    $ metric("noelle_frameworks_survived_breaking", delta=1)
    $ nudge_poly("noelle", "want_as_register", delta=1)
    $ scene_mark(_current_scene_id, "exited")

    return


